text: Koun Wick (10 November 1917 – 27 December 1999) was a Cambodian statesman and diplomat who served as Minister of Foreign Affairs from 1970 to 1972 and from 1964 to 1965. He was a cousin of former prime minister Chau Sen Cocsal Chhum.https://www.rulers.org/indexc2.html ==References== Category:1917 births Category:1999 deaths Category:20th-century Cambodian politicians Category:Cambodian diplomats Category:Cambodian expatriates in France Category:Foreign ministers of Cambodia Category:Khmer Republic
